==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Latitudinarianism
<hw>Lat`i*tu`di*na"ri*an*ism</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A
latitudinarian system or condition; freedom of opinion in matters
pertaining to religious belief.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Fierce sectarianism bred fierce <qex>latitudinarianism</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>De Quincey.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>He [Ammonius Saccas] plunged into the wildest
<qex>latitudinarianism</qex> of opinion.</q> <rj><qau>J. S.
Harford.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Latitudinous</ent>⟦br⟧
